2026-04-20 03:23:35 [DEBUG] llm.engine: RESULT: answer="The function `resolve_item_reference` handles three main cases:\n\n1. **No reference provided**: If `reference` is None and a last item ID exists in session, it returns that ID with a fallback message. Otherwise, it lists available items or provides guidance on which item to refer to.\n\n2. **Deterministic resolution**: When a reference is provided, it calls `engine.resolve_candidates()` to resolve the reference deterministically. It then retrieves and validates the chosen item's label.\n\n3. **Error handling**: If no item is found matching the reference, it lists all valid items and informs the user about the unrecognized reference.\n\nThe function returns a tuple containing either the resolved item ID or None (for error cases), along with an appropriate message."
